{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Sebastian Klingler | Front-end Engineer","author":"Sebastian Klingler"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"7a902137-3be0-583c-b37c-9d77090accf1","html":"<p><a href=\"http://www.the-tacky.com/\">Tacky</a> is a scenario discovery and management tool. It allows you to create a hierarchical description of user interactions with a system and transform it into a list of discrete test cases.</p>\n<h2>Motivation</h2>\n<p>The linear way of writing test scenarios leaves a lot to be desired. Representing the state of a system without abstracting away the steps to get there becomes tedious and error-prone. </p>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<p>In Tacky, you create rows (known as layers) that contain steps (known as cases). A layer can have multiple cases. For example, a todo app could look like this:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/tacky-35bb635df941324433d0963c71b23ea1-cc1f4.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 56.14754098360656%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Tacky\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/tacky-35bb635df941324433d0963c71b23ea1-fb8a0.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/tacky-35bb635df941324433d0963c71b23ea1-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/tacky-35bb635df941324433d0963c71b23ea1-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/tacky-35bb635df941324433d0963c71b23ea1-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/tacky-35bb635df941324433d0963c71b23ea1-526de.png 885w,\n/static/tacky-35bb635df941324433d0963c71b23ea1-fa2eb.png 1180w,\n/static/tacky-35bb635df941324433d0963c71b23ea1-cc1f4.png 1464w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Regarding the above as a tree, the paths that need to be followed to exhaustively test the system are those from root to leaf. A tester can mark the branches as they are completed and know at a glance which paths still need testing. Tacky can also display the branches as a list of discrete test cases:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/tacky2-b8d866335b76f3dabecccb99b5b6fafe-f6e09.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 108.75656742556919%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Tacky\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/tacky2-b8d866335b76f3dabecccb99b5b6fafe-fb8a0.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/tacky2-b8d866335b76f3dabecccb99b5b6fafe-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/tacky2-b8d866335b76f3dabecccb99b5b6fafe-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/tacky2-b8d866335b76f3dabecccb99b5b6fafe-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/tacky2-b8d866335b76f3dabecccb99b5b6fafe-526de.png 885w,\n/static/tacky2-b8d866335b76f3dabecccb99b5b6fafe-f6e09.png 1142w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Stack</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://vuejs.org/\">Vue.js</a> was chosen because of how quickly a prototype can be built with it. There is just enough “magic” to make putting together an application a breeze.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://vuex.vuejs.org/\">Vuex</a> was used as the state container. Having a centralized store makes it easy to save and share Tacky boards.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://expressjs.com/\">Express</a> was used to serve the application.</p>\n<h1>Contribute</h1>\n<p>I’m open to any and all contribution! Find the repo <a href=\"https://gitlab.com/sliptype/tacky\">here</a></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Tacky","date":"September 20, 2017"}}},"pageContext":{"jsonName":"tacky-8e1","internalComponentName":"ComponentTacky","path":"/tacky/","component":"/Users/sebastian/workspace/sliptype.github.io/src/templates/blog-post.js","componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","context":{"slug":"/tacky/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/Hallpass/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Hallpass"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/smartcert/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"SmartCert"}}},"updatedAt":1539741902868,"pluginCreator___NODE":"Plugin default-site-plugin","pluginCreatorId":"Plugin default-site-plugin","componentPath":"/Users/sebastian/workspace/sliptype.github.io/src/templates/blog-post.js","slug":"/tacky/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/Hallpass/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Hallpass"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/smartcert/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"SmartCert"}}}}